devdoc.details: This library handles deposits to and withdrawals from the liquidity pools that power RariFund as well as currency exchanges via 0x.

approveTo0x(address,uint256).details: Approves tokens to 0x without spending gas on every deposit.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be approved.
params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token to be approved.

approveToPool(uint8,address,uint256).details: Approves tokens to the pool without spending gas on every deposit.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be approved.
params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token to be approved.

depositToPool(uint8,address,uint256).details: Deposits funds to the specified pool.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be deposited.
params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token to be deposited.

getPoolBalance(uint8,address).details: Returns the calling address's balance of the specified currency in the specified pool. Ideally, we can add the view modifier, but Compound's `getUnderlyingBalance` function (called by `CompoundPoolController.getBalance`) potentially modifies the state.

params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token.

marketSell0xOrdersFillOrKill(LibOrder.Or.details: Fills 0x exchange orders up to a certain amount of input and up to a certain price. We should be able to make this function external and use calldata for all parameters, but Solidity does not support calldata structs (https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/5479).

params.orders: The limit orders to be filled in ascending order of price.
params.protocolFee: The protocol fee in ETH to pay to 0x.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: The amount of the taker asset to sell (excluding taker fees).

marketSell0xOrdersFillOrKill(LibOrder.Or.return: Array containing the input amount sold and output amount bought.

withdrawAllFromPool(uint8,address).details: Withdraws all funds from the specified pool.

params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token to be withdrawn.

withdrawFromPool(uint8,address,uint256).details: Withdraws funds from the specified pool.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be withdrawn.
params.erc20Contract: The ERC20 contract of the token to be withdrawn.
